racks in the garage door frame.";i:18;s:105:"Now you can align the track so it is perfectly vertical by tapping it at the bottom with a rubber mallet.";i:19;s:94:"Standard residential torsion springs are found on a shaft above the center of the garage door.";i:20;s:65:"These springs typically come in 1 34 2 and 2 14 inside diameters.";i:21;s:130:"If you want to know how your torsion spring system works on your door watch our introduction to garage door torsion springs video.";i:22;s:82:"Extension springs attach at the top end to the garage door track support brackets.";i:23;s:21:"The other end of the.";i:24;s:44:"Spring is attached to a pulley using a fork.";i:25;s:58:"A cable that attaches to the bottom bracket on the bottom.";i:26;s:101:"Panel of each side of the garage door travels up the height of the garage door around one pulley and.";i:27;s:30:"Then around the spring pulley.";i:28;s:34:"Each garage door has four pulleys.";i:29;s:79:"On each side of the tracks two of these pulleys with pulley forks are attached.";i:30;s:102:"Meanwhile the other two are stationary pulleys on top of the horizontal track facing the radius track.";i:31;s:116:"When pulleys are worn out garage doors cannot function properly disabling its full potential in opening and closing.";i:32;s:24:"Step 1 - Start The Task.";i:33;s:39:"Check out replacement cables on Amazon.";i:34;s:171:"To make the garage door rise with much the same ease as it did when it was first installed your first task is to release the springs by using the clamp to the door roller.";i:35;s:28:"Do this at the lowest point.";i:36;s:27:"Step 2 - Check the Pulleys.";i:37;s:85:"Once this is accomplished you need to make sure that the pulleys dont need replacing.";i:38;s:36:"Troubleshooting Garage Door Springs.";i:39;s:49:"Adjusting garage door springs is a common repair.";i:40;s:62:"Garage door springs are used to offset the weight of the door.";i:41;s:55:"Without the springs the door is very difficult to lift.";i:42;s:103:"